<subSubSection id="C30D654BFFD9FFFC9A0AF863F93B31CA" lastPageId="73" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA836C0FFD9FFFC9A0AF863F93B31CA" blockId="72.[151,1437,150,2035]" lastBlockId="73.[151,1437,150,643]" lastPageId="73" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFD9FFFD9A0AF863F91C37AE" bold="true" box="[631,861,1937,1963]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Mexican Lampfish</emphasis>
. To 
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFD9FFFD9BE4F863F99437A9" box="[921,981,1937,1964]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="9.0">9 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFD9FFFD9B94F863FE7137A9" box="[1001,1072,1937,1964]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.89" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="in" value="3.5">3.5 in</quantity>
) SL (Personal communication: Scripps Institution of Oceanography Fish Collection, La Jolla, California). British Columbia (Gillespie 1993) to off southern 
<collectingCountry id="F3007650FFD9FFFD9908F82BFB8A37F6" box="[373,459,2009,2035]" name="Mexico" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FFD9FFFD99A7F82BF96537F6" author="Rodriguez-Grana, L. &amp; Herrera, G. &amp; Herrera, L. &amp; Castro, L. R." box="[474,804,2009,2035]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="1455 - 1461" refId="ref317172" refString="Rodriguez-Grana, L., Herrera, G., Herrera, L. &amp; Castro, L. R. (2004) Divergence of two forms of Triphoturus in the eastern Pacific based on mtDNA cytochrome b gene sequence and larval morphology. Journal of Fish Biology, 64, 1455 - 1461. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 0022 - 1112.2004.00413. x" type="journal article" year="2004">
Rodríguez-Graña 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFD9FFFD9ADAF828F8A137F6" box="[679,736,2009,2035]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
), including Gulf of California (
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FFD9FFFC9CF5F82BFBFF30B4" author="De La Cruz-Aguero, J. &amp; Galvan-Magana, F." lastPageId="73" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="25 - 31" refId="ref274229" refString="De La Cruz-Aguero, J. &amp; Galvan-Magana, F. (1992) Peces mesopelagicos de la costa occidental de Baja California sur y del Gulfo de California. Anales del Instituto de Ciencias del Mar y Limnologia, 19, 25 - 31." type="journal article" year="1992">De La Cruz-Agüero and Galván-Magaña 1992</bibRefCitation>
). Depth: surface to perhaps 
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFD8FFFC9A80FF65F91A30B4" box="[765,859,151,177]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.882" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" unit="m" value="2882.0">2,882 m</quantity>
(
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFD8FFFC9B17FF64F98730B7" box="[874,966,150,178]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8812743999999997" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" unit="ft" value="9453.0">9,453 ft</quantity>
) (min.: Personal communication: Scripps Institution of Oceanography Fish Collection, La Jolla, California; max.: Personal communication: Los Angeles County Museum of Natural History Fish Collection, Los Angeles, California). Maximum depth poorly known, most captures appear to be in 
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFD8FFFC9A68FEF0F8303119" box="[533,625,258,284]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" unit="m" value="1000.0">1,000 m</quantity>
(
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFD8FFFC9A02FEF0F89B3118" box="[639,730,258,285]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.99744" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" unit="ft" value="3280.0">3,280 ft</quantity>
) or less. Deeper records, such as 
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFD8FFFC9C2DFEF0FEEC3119" box="[1104,1197,258,284]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" unit="m" value="4100.0">4,100 m</quantity>
(
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFD8FFFC9CC6FEF0FF653118" box="[1211,1316,258,285]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0989504" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" unit="ft" value="13448.0">13,448 ft</quantity>
) (Personal communication: Scripps Institution of Oceanography Fish Collection, La Jolla, California), are based on the maximum depth fished by a midwater trawl and may represent a catch shallower than the maximum depth. 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D43FFD8FFFC98BBFE9FF8153182" authority="(Garman 1899)" baseAuthorityName="Garman" baseAuthorityYear="1899" box="[198,596,365,391]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Myctophidae" genus="Triphoturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myctophiformes" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oculeus">
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFD8FFFC98BBFE9FFBE43182" box="[198,421,365,391]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Triphoturus oculeus</emphasis>
(Garman 1899)
</taxonomicName>
has been considered to be synonymous with 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D43FFD8FFFC9C3CFE9FFB4031AE" authority="Gilbert, 1890" authorityName="Gilbert" authorityYear="1890" class="Actinopterygii" family="Myctophidae" genus="Triphoturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myctophiformes" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFD8FFFC9C3CFE9FFF003182" box="[1089,1345,365,391]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Triphoturus mexicanus</emphasis>
Gilbert, 1890
</taxonomicName>
. However, on the basis of both DNA and larvae characters Rodríquez-Graña 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFD8FFFC9C0EFE60FEED31AE" box="[1139,1196,401,427]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">et al.</emphasis>
(2004) separated the two species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D43FFD8FFFC992BFE46F87631CB" baseAuthorityName="Garman" baseAuthorityYear="1899" box="[342,567,436,462]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Myctophidae" genus="Triphoturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myctophiformes" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oculeus">
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFD8FFFC992BFE46F87631CB" box="[342,567,436,462]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Triphoturus oculeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found from 
<geoCoordinate id="EE235007FFD8FFFC9AA0FE47F95931CA" box="[733,792,437,463]" degrees="13" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" precision="55555" value="13.0">13°N</geoCoordinate>
to 
<geoCoordinate id="EE235007FFD8FFFC9B41FE46F93731CA" box="[828,886,436,463]" degrees="35" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" precision="55555" value="-35.0">35°S</geoCoordinate>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
